            Tags = """["kanban","jobs","board","production","drag-and-drop","real-time"]""",
            ContentJson = """
{"body":"## Kanban Board Overview\n\nThe Kanban Board is the operational heart of Forge. Every job in your shop — whether it's a customer production order, an R&D prototype, a maintenance task, or an internal project — lives on the board and moves through stages from left to right as work progresses. The board gives you a real-time, at-a-glance view of everything happening in your shop.\n\n### Track Types\n\nThe board is organized by **track types**. Each track type represents a distinct workflow with its own set of stages. Forge ships with four built-in track types:\n\n- **Production** — The primary workflow for customer jobs. Stages follow the quote-to-cash flow: Quote Requested → Quoted (Estimate) → Order Confirmed (Sales Order) → Materials Ordered (PO) → Materials Received → In Production → QC/Review → Shipped (Invoice) → Invoiced/Sent → Payment Received (Payment).\n- **R&D/Tooling** — For research, development, and tooling projects. Includes iteration tracking (version count and notes) for prototype cycles.\n- **Maintenance** — For equipment maintenance, facility repairs, and upkeep tasks.\n- **Other** — A catch-all for anything that doesn't fit the above categories.\n\nAdmins can create custom track types with custom stages from the Admin settings. Each track type can have its own stage colors, WIP limits, and irreversible stage flags.\n\nYou switch between track types using the **track type buttons** in the page header. The board reloads instantly when you switch, and keeps updating in real time.\n\n### Stages and Columns\n\nEach stage in a track type becomes a **column** on the board. Columns display from left to right in sort order. Each column header shows:\n\n- **Stage name** — The name of the stage.\n- **Job count** — How many jobs are currently in that column.\n- **WIP limit** — If configured, the maximum recommended jobs for the column. When exceeded, the count turns red as a visual warning.\n- **Lock icon** — Appears on irreversible stages. Jobs cannot be moved backward out of an irreversible stage (e.g., once an invoice is created at the 'Shipped' stage, you can't move the job back to 'In Production').\n- **Color stripe** — A colored top border matching the stage color for quick visual identification.\n\nEmpty columns show an empty state message encouraging you to drag jobs in.\n\n### Job Cards\n\nEach job on the board is represented by a **job card**. Cards are compact but information-dense:\n\n- **Left border color** — Indicates priority: gray (Low), teal (Normal), orange (High), red (Urgent).\n- **Job number** — Clickable link that opens the full job detail dialog. Auto-generated sequential number (e.g., JOB-0001).\n- **Title** — The job's title text.\n- **Cover photo** — Optional image displayed above the card content. Uploaded via the detail panel.\n- **Hold indicator** — A pause icon appears when the job has active holds, with a tooltip listing hold reasons.\n- **Overdue warning** — A yellow warning icon appears when the job's due date has passed.\n- **Footer indicators:**\n  - Who it's assigned to (their initials)\n  - Customer name\n  - Billing status icon (invoiced/uninvoiced)\n  - Accounting document reference (e.g., QuickBooks invoice number)\n  - Disposition icon (if the job has been disposed)\n  - Sub-jobs count with tree icon\n  - Due date (turns red when overdue)\n\n### Drag-and-Drop\n\nCards can be **dragged between columns** to move jobs through stages. The card moves the moment you drop it. If the move isn't allowed — like trying to move backward out of a one-way stage — the card snaps back to where it was.\n\nWithin a column, you can **reorder cards** by dragging them up or down. Position changes are saved automatically.\n\nWhen a job moves to the **final stage** of its track type, the system automatically sets the job's completed date. Moving it backward clears the completed date.\n\nIf the target stage is set up to create an **accounting document** (e.g., an invoice at the 'Shipped' stage), moving a job there automatically queues that document to be created in your connected accounting system.\n\n### Multi-Select and Bulk Actions\n\nHold **Ctrl** (or **Cmd** on Mac) and click cards to select multiple jobs. A selection count badge and a **bulk action bar** appear at the bottom of the screen. Bulk actions include:\n\n- **Move** — Move all selected jobs to a chosen stage.\n- **Assign** — Assign all selected jobs to a team member (or unassign).\n- **Priority** — Set priority on all selected jobs.\n- **Archive** — Archive all selected jobs (with confirmation dialog).\n\nClick any card without Ctrl to deselect all. Click the X button in the bulk bar to clear the selection.\n\n### Board View vs. Team (Swimlane) View\n\nThe board has two view modes, toggled via icons in the header:\n\n- **Board View** (default) — Traditional kanban columns. Best for seeing the flow of work through stages.\n- **Team View** — A swimlane grid where each row is a team member and each column is a stage. Cards appear at the intersection of their assignee and current stage. Includes an 'Unassigned' row. You can drag cards between cells to simultaneously change stage and assignee.\n\n### Filtering\n\n- **Team Members** multi-select — Filter the board to show only jobs assigned to specific people.\n- **My Work** toggle — Quick filter to show only jobs assigned to you. Persists as a user preference.\n\n### Real-Time Sync\n\nThe board updates live. When another user creates a job, moves a card, updates a job, or reorders cards, your board refreshes on its own — no manual refresh needed.\n\nIf the connection drops, a yellow 'Reconnecting...' banner appears at the top of the page. If it can't reconnect, the banner turns red.\n\n### Barcode Scanner Integration\n\nIf you have a USB barcode scanner connected, scanning a job number barcode while on the kanban page will automatically find and open that job's details. No need to click into a field first — just scan while the board is up.\n\n### Job Detail Panel\n\nClicking a job number opens the **full job details** in a window split into two columns:\n\n**Left column (main content):**\n- Title and description\n- R&D iteration badge (for R&D/Tooling track)\n- Disposition info (if disposed)\n- Subtasks with checkbox completion\n- Sub-jobs list with entity links\n- BOM explosion button (if the job has a linked part)\n- Linked cards (related jobs, blocking jobs, parent/child relationships)\n- Parts list with search and add\n- Cost analysis summary\n- Operation time analysis\n- Activity log, comments, notes, and history\n\n**Right column (sidebar):**\n- Status timeline with holds\n- Disposition button\n- Barcode/QR code info\n- Details metadata (priority, assignee with quick-change menu, customer, due date, start date, track type, linked part, parent job)\n- File attachments with drag-and-drop upload\n- Time entries logged against the job\n\n### Create / Edit Job Dialog\n\nThe create dialog collects: Title (required, max 200 chars), Description, Track Type (create only), Customer, Assignee, Priority, and Due Date. The edit dialog is identical but without Track Type (you can't change a job's track type after creation).\n\nDraft auto-save is enabled — if you close the dialog accidentally, your form data is recovered on next visit.\n\n### Sharing a Link\n\nWhen you open a job's details, the web address updates to point at that job. Copy it from the address bar to share a direct link to that job. Bookmarks and the browser's back and forward buttons all work as expected.","sections":[]}
"""
        });

