{"appRoute":"/kanban","startButtonLabel":"Tour Kanban Board","steps":[{"element":"[data-tour='track-type-switcher']","popover":{"title":"Track Type Selector","description":"Switch between board workflows here. Each track type — Production, R&D/Tooling, Maintenance, Other, or your own — has its own stages. Click a track type to load its board. The one you're viewing stays highlighted.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".view-toggle","popover":{"title":"Board View and Team View","description":"Switch between two layouts. Board View lays out stages as columns with cards stacked in each. Team View shows a grid: one row per team member, one column per stage, and each card sits where its person and stage meet. You can drag cards in both.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"[data-tour='board-filters']","popover":{"title":"Team Members Filter","description":"Show only certain people's jobs. Pick one or more team members to narrow the board; leave it empty to see everyone's jobs. In Team View, this also sets which rows appear.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".my-work-btn","popover":{"title":"My Work Button","description":"Show only the jobs assigned to you. The board remembers this — it stays on even after you leave and come back. Click it again to show everyone's jobs.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"[data-testid='new-job-btn']","popover":{"title":"Create New Job","description":"Open the new-job form. Enter a title (required), and optionally a description, customer, assignee, priority, and due date, then pick a track type. The job number fills in for you, and the job starts in the first stage. Close the form by accident and your entries are saved for next time.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"[data-tour='board-columns']","popover":{"title":"The Board and Its Hint Bar","description":"This bar reminds you that cards can be dragged. Hold Ctrl (or Cmd on Mac) and click cards to select several at once. Once cards are selected, the hint bar becomes an action bar for working on them together.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"[data-tour='wip-limit']","popover":{"title":"Column Header","description":"Each column header shows the stage name, how many jobs are in it, and a suggested limit if one is set. Go over that limit and the count turns red as a heads-up. A lock icon means the stage is one-way — jobs can't move back out of it. The colored strip on top matches the stage's color.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"[data-tour='job-card']","popover":{"title":"Job Card","description":"Each card sums up a job. The left edge is colored by priority: gray for Low, teal for Normal, orange for High, red for Urgent. Up top is the job number, plus a pause icon if the job is on hold and a warning icon if it's overdue. Along the bottom you'll see who it's assigned to, the customer, billing status, any sub-jobs, and the due date. Click the job number to open its full details. Ctrl+click to select several cards.","side":"right"}},{"element":".column","popover":{"title":"Drag and Drop","description":"Drag a card to another column to move the job to that stage. It moves right away; if the move isn't allowed — like going backward out of a one-way stage — it slides back. Drag a card up or down to reorder it, and its place is saved for you. In Team View, dragging a card can change its stage and its assignee at once.","side":"top"}}]}
"""
