{"passingScore":80,"questionsPerQuiz":10,"shuffleOptions":true,"showExplanationsAfterSubmit":true,"questions":[{"id":"kb1","text":"You need to create a new production job for a customer order. What is the correct sequence?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Go to the Kanban board, click 'New Job', fill in Title, select Production track type, choose the customer, set priority, and click Save","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Go to Admin → Jobs → Add New and enter all the job details there"},{"id":"c","text":"Create a Sales Order first, then the system auto-generates the job"},{"id":"d","text":"Go to the Backlog page and drag a card to the board"}],"explanation":"Jobs are created directly from the Kanban board using the 'New Job' button. Fill in the required Title, select the track type (Production for customer orders), and optionally set customer, assignee, priority, and due date. The job number is auto-generated and the job starts in the first stage."},{"id":"kb2","text":"A job card on the board has a red left border and a yellow warning triangle. What does this tell you?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The job is Urgent priority and is overdue","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"The job has errors and needs immediate attention from an admin"},{"id":"c","text":"The job is on hold and cannot be moved"},{"id":"d","text":"The job has been flagged for quality review"}],"explanation":"The left border color indicates priority: red = Urgent. The yellow warning triangle indicates the job's due date has passed (overdue). Together they tell you this is an urgent job that is already late."},{"id":"kb3","text":"You try to drag a job card backward from the 'Shipped' column, but it snaps back to its original position. Why?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The 'Shipped' stage is marked as irreversible because an accounting document (invoice) was created at that stage","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"You don't have permission to move cards on this board"},{"id":"c","text":"The job is locked because it has a customer assigned"},{"id":"d","text":"Backward moves are never allowed on the kanban board"}],"explanation":"Stages can be marked as irreversible (shown with a lock icon). The 'Shipped' stage typically creates an invoice, making it irreversible — you can't undo the accounting document. The card snaps back to its position with an error. Backward moves are allowed from non-irreversible stages."},{"id":"kb4","text":"You want to reassign 8 jobs from one team member to another as quickly as possible. What is the most efficient method?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Ctrl+Click all 8 job cards, then use the Assign button in the bulk action bar to select the new assignee","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Open each job's detail dialog one at a time and change the assignee"},{"id":"c","text":"Use the Team View, create a filter for the old assignee, then drag each card to the new assignee's row one by one"},{"id":"d","text":"Go to Admin → Users → Reassign Jobs and enter the new assignee"}],"explanation":"Multi-select with Ctrl+Click lets you select multiple cards, then the bulk action bar's Assign button reassigns all of them in one operation. This is the fastest way to bulk-reassign jobs."},{"id":"kb5","text":"A column header shows '7 / 5' in red. What does this mean and what should you do?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The column has 7 jobs but the WIP limit is 5 — the stage is overloaded and you should move some jobs forward or redistribute work","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"7 jobs out of 5 have been completed in this stage — the stage is performing well"},{"id":"c","text":"The column has 5 jobs but the maximum allowed is 7 — you have room for 2 more"},{"id":"d","text":"7 jobs failed validation and 5 are blocked — contact an admin"}],"explanation":"WIP (Work-In-Progress) limits are advisory thresholds set per-stage. When exceeded (7 jobs vs. 5 limit), the count turns red as a visual warning that the stage is overloaded. This indicates a bottleneck — consider moving jobs forward, rebalancing work, or addressing blockers."},{"id":"kb6","text":"What happens when you move a job to the final stage of its track type?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The system automatically stamps the job with today's date as its completed date","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"The job is permanently archived and removed from the board"},{"id":"c","text":"An invoice is automatically generated and sent to the customer"},{"id":"d","text":"Nothing special — it's treated the same as any other stage move"}],"explanation":"When a job reaches the final stage, the system stamps it with today's completed date. The job stays on the board — it isn't archived automatically. If it's later moved backward from the final stage, that completed date is cleared."},{"id":"kb7","text":"You're viewing the Kanban board and another team member creates a new job. How does your board update?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The board updates on its own, in real time — the new card appears without you needing to refresh","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"You need to manually click a Refresh button to see the new job"},{"id":"c","text":"The board checks the server every 30 seconds and updates on the next cycle"},{"id":"d","text":"You need to navigate away and back to the kanban page to see the update"}],"explanation":"The board updates live. When anyone creates a job, moves a card, updates a job, or reorders cards, every open board refreshes on its own — no manual refresh needed."},{"id":"kb8","text":"What is the difference between Board View and Team View?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Board View shows columns by stage with cards stacked vertically; Team View shows a swimlane grid where rows are team members and columns are stages","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Board View is for managers and Team View is for individual contributors — they show different data based on your role"},{"id":"c","text":"Board View shows all jobs and Team View only shows your assigned jobs"},{"id":"d","text":"Board View is the live board and Team View is a planning/forecast view"}],"explanation":"Board View is the traditional kanban column layout. Team View adds a user dimension — each row represents a team member (plus an Unassigned row), and cards appear at the intersection of their assignee and stage. You can drag cards in both views, and in Team View, dragging between cells can change both stage and assignee simultaneously."},{"id":"kb9","text":"You open a job detail dialog and want to quickly reassign the job without opening the edit dialog. How?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Click the assignee in the sidebar Details section to open a menu, then pick the new person","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"You must click the Edit button and change the assignee in the edit form"},{"id":"c","text":"Drag the job card to a different row in Team View"},{"id":"d","text":"Right-click the job card and select 'Reassign' from the menu"}],"explanation":"Click the assignee in the details sidebar and a menu opens with everyone on your team plus an 'Unassign' option. Pick someone and the job is reassigned right away — no need to open the full edit form."},{"id":"kb10","text":"A job has a linked part and no child jobs. What does the 'Explode BOM' button do?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Creates child jobs from the part's bill of materials — each 'Make' BOM line becomes a child job on the same track type","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Breaks the job into smaller subtasks based on the part's operations"},{"id":"c","text":"Generates a purchase order for all the materials needed for the part"},{"id":"d","text":"Opens a 3D view of the part's assembly structure"}],"explanation":"BOM Explosion reads the bill of materials from the job's linked part and creates a child job for each 'Make' BOM line (on the same track type). 'Buy' lines surface as purchasing suggestions and 'Stock' lines auto-reserve available inventory rather than spawning jobs. This is useful for complex assemblies where each made component needs its own production tracking. The button only appears when the job has a linked part and no existing child jobs."},{"id":"kb11","text":"You accidentally closed the Create Job dialog after filling in several fields. What happens to your form data?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The form auto-saves your entries as a draft — they come back with a banner the next time you open it","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"All data is lost and you need to re-enter everything"},{"id":"c","text":"The data is held in memory for 60 seconds if you click 'New Job' again"},{"id":"d","text":"A prompt stops you from closing if the form has unsaved data"}],"explanation":"The new/edit job form saves what you type as a draft as you go. If you close it by accident (or the browser crashes), the next time you open it a 'Recovered unsaved changes' banner appears and your entries are restored."},{"id":"kb12","text":"How do you share a direct link to a specific job with a coworker?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Open the job's details — the web address updates to point at that job. Copy it from the address bar and share it.","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Click a Share button in the job's details to generate a shareable link"},{"id":"c","text":"Right-click the job card and select 'Copy Link'"},{"id":"d","text":"You can only share job numbers — there are no direct links to specific jobs"}],"explanation":"When you open a job's details, the web address updates to point at that job. Anyone who opens that address lands on the board with the job's details already open. It works with bookmarks and browser history too."},{"id":"kb13","text":"You scan a barcode with a USB scanner while on the Kanban board. What happens?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The system looks for a job matching the scanned number and, if it finds one, opens its details","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"The scanned value is entered into the team members filter field"},{"id":"c","text":"Nothing — barcode scanning only works on the Inventory and Parts pages"},{"id":"d","text":"A new job is created with the scanned value as the title"}],"explanation":"On the board, a scanned barcode is matched against the job numbers on the current board. If one matches, its details open with a confirmation message. If none match, you get an error message instead."},{"id":"kb14","text":"What are the three types of job links you can create between cards?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Related to (general relationship), Blocks (dependency), and Parent of (hierarchy)","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Duplicate, Predecessor, and Successor"},{"id":"c","text":"Depends on, Required by, and Same as"},{"id":"d","text":"Before, After, and Parallel"}],"explanation":"Forge supports three link types: 'Related to' for general relationships between jobs, 'Blocks' for dependency tracking (this job blocks the linked job), and 'Parent of' for hierarchical structures (this job is the parent of the linked job)."},{"id":"kb15","text":"When you move a job card to a stage that has an accounting document type configured (e.g., Invoice), what happens automatically?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"If an accounting system is connected and the job's customer is linked to it, the document (such as an invoice) is queued to be created there","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"An invoice is immediately created and sent to the customer via email"},{"id":"c","text":"The job card turns green to indicate it has been invoiced"},{"id":"d","text":"Nothing automatic — you must manually create the invoice from the Sales Orders page"}],"explanation":"When a stage is set up to create an accounting document, moving a job there queues it — but only if an accounting system is connected, the job has a customer, and that customer is linked to the accounting system. When all three are true, the document is queued for creation."},{"id":"kb16","text":"You see a pause icon (⏸) in a job card's header. What does this indicate?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The job has one or more active holds — hover over the icon to see the hold reasons in a tooltip","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"The job's timer is currently paused"},{"id":"c","text":"The job is waiting for customer approval"},{"id":"d","text":"The job is in a paused/maintenance stage and cannot be moved"}],"explanation":"The pause circle icon appears on job cards that have active holds. Holds are set via the Status Timeline in the detail dialog (e.g., 'Waiting for Materials', 'Customer Review'). Hovering over the icon shows a tooltip listing all active hold reasons."},{"id":"kb17","text":"In Team View, you drag a card from Alice's row in the 'In Production' column to Bob's row in the 'QC/Review' column. What happens?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The job is both moved to the QC/Review stage and reassigned from Alice to Bob simultaneously","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Only the stage changes to QC/Review — the assignee stays as Alice"},{"id":"c","text":"Only the assignee changes to Bob — the stage stays at In Production"},{"id":"d","text":"An error occurs — you can only change one attribute at a time"}],"explanation":"In Team View, each cell is where a person (row) and a stage (column) meet. Dragging a card from one cell to another can change both the stage and who it's assigned to in a single move."},{"id":"kb18","text":"You want to see only your assigned jobs on the board and have this preference persist across sessions. Which approach is correct?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Click the 'My Work' toggle button in the header — it filters to your jobs and saves the preference so it persists when you return","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Use the Team Members filter and select only yourself — but you'll need to reselect each time you visit"},{"id":"c","text":"Go to Account → Settings → Default Board Filter and set it to 'My Jobs Only'"},{"id":"d","text":"There is no way to persist board filters — you must set them each time"}],"explanation":"The 'My Work' button filters the board to just your jobs and remembers the choice, so it stays on the next time you come back. The Team Members filter can do the same thing, but it doesn't stick between visits."},{"id":"kb19","text":"What are the five disposition types when disposing a completed job?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Ship to Customer, Add to Inventory, Capitalize as Asset, Scrap, and Hold for Review","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Complete, Cancel, Return, Rework, and Archive"},{"id":"c","text":"Deliver, Store, Transfer, Dispose, and Recycle"},{"id":"d","text":"Accept, Reject, Rework, Quarantine, and Ship"}],"explanation":"Job disposition determines what happens to the job's output: Ship to Customer (deliver the product), Add to Inventory (stock the finished goods), Capitalize as Asset (register as a tooling/equipment asset), Scrap (discard as waste), or Hold for Review (keep for further evaluation). Each has different downstream effects."},{"id":"kb20","text":"The connection banner at the top of the page turns yellow and says 'Reconnecting...'. What is happening and what should you do?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The connection to the server dropped and is reconnecting on its own — wait a few seconds and live updates resume once it's back","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"The server is shutting down for maintenance — save your work and close the application"},{"id":"c","text":"Your session has expired — you need to log in again"},{"id":"d","text":"Another user has taken control of the board — you are now in read-only mode"}],"explanation":"Yellow 'Reconnecting...' means the connection to the server dropped (a network blip, a server restart, and so on) and it's trying to reconnect on its own. It usually comes back within seconds. If it can't, the banner turns red. The board still works, but won't get live updates until it reconnects."}]}
"""
